<p>The <code>right</code> function returns the last N characters of a string.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo $sampleText | right(10){close}</pre>
<p>Last 10: <b>{echo $sampleText | right(10)}</b></p>

<h2>File Extension</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'document.txt' | right(3){close}</pre>
<p>Extension: <b>{echo 'document.txt' | right(3)}</b></p>

<h2>Last Digits</h2>
<pre>{open}echo '1234567890' | right(4){close}</pre>
<p>Last 4: <b>{echo '1234567890' | right(4)}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo $sampleText | right(15) | upper{close}</pre>
<p>Last 15 uppercase: <b>{echo $sampleText | right(15) | upper}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo $filePath | right(10) | lower{close}</pre>
<p>End of path: <b>{echo $filePath | right(10) | lower}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo 'HELLO WORLD' | right(5) | lower | capitalize{close}</pre>
<p>Last word formatted: <b>{echo 'HELLO WORLD' | right(5) | lower | capitalize}</b></p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>If the string is shorter than N, the entire string is returned.</p>
